text_clean: Joby Aviation, Inc., a California-based company developing electric air taxis for commercial passenger service, acquired a manufacturing facility in the Dayton, Ohio area spanning more than 700,000 square feet. The facility is ready for immediate use and will support Joby’s plan to double production to four aircraft per month in 2027, while also providing space for significant future growth. The factory complements Joby’s existing production facilities in California and Ohio, with operations in the new facility expected to begin this year. In July 2025, Joby completed an expanded manufacturing facility in Marina, California, and in October confirmed the start of propeller blade production in Ohio. To support the planned doubling of production, Joby began procurement of the capital equipment required to double manufacturing capacity last month. Supply Technologies LLC, a global supply chain management company and business of Park-Ohio Holdings Corp., will invest nearly $5.8 million in a consolidation project in Union, Ohio, creating 57 new jobs and retaining 38 existing jobs. The new 375,000-square-foot distribution center will house advanced warehouse operations, a quality and engineering lab, and an innovation center to serve customers and warehouses across the United States, Canada, and Mexico. Hiring for the facility is expected to begin in early 2026, with an official opening targeted for July 1, 2026. Riverain Technologies, Inc. will create 48 jobs and retain 29 with its expansion in Miamisburg, Ohio. The company develops AI-powered tools for radiology, including ClearRead™, which healthcare organizations across Ohio use to improve detection of prevalent and deadly cardiothoracic diseases; these organizations include Kettering Health Network, TriHealth, multiple Veterans Hospitals throughout Ohio, Mercy Hospital, and University Hospitals in Cleveland, with which Riverain collaborates on research initiatives to advance early detection and treatment of thoracic diseases.

The lawsuit was first disclosed in November 2025, and no hearing date has been set. Archer stated it plans to continue vigorously defending the matter. reason: 文本中明确提到‘丰田可能提供约4亿美元资金支持’，并指出该款项与S4符合性构型首飞及/或首次FAA监督下有人驾驶飞行直接挂钩。虽然金额为‘约4亿美元’，但关键在于指标4的定义要求‘确认Toyota第二期$2.5亿投资条件满足/到账’。此处‘4亿美元’显著高于$2.5亿阈值，且明确说明该资金与具体制造/取证里程碑（S4首飞、FAA监督飞行）挂钩，符合‘二期资金到位’的核心判断标准。此外，文本还提到‘JOBY与丰田存在合作关系’以及丰田董事长关注JOBY S4座椅设计，侧面佐证了制造联盟关系的深化。因此，尽管措辞为‘可能提供’，但结合‘直接挂钩’这一强关联表述，可合理推断该资金支持已满足特定条件，符合指标4中‘确认...投资条件满足/到账’的要求。
